parameters: Matsuri
"Just spend your time as you like."
Matsuri
"Welcome back. Did you find anything interesting?"
Hinori
"Matsuri-chan, there's something I want to ask you.."
Matsuri
"Hmm, what is it?"
Hinori
"Do you.. like your father?"
In response to Hinori's question, Matsuri smiled a little awkwardly.
Matsuri

"Umm.. not really, is it? I don't hate him, but he's always so noisy. He
tells me to wear more calm clothes and stuff. It's my own business, right?"
Hinori
"So, is that so.."
Ao
"..If I were your father, I might say the same thing."
Matsuri

"He's just being overprotective. I mean, I'm a good girl who listens to
Daddy, but he's always worried about stuff like this. I understand why he's
concerned, but still.."

Matsuri's face, as she listed her complaints about her father in that way,
even seemed somewhat amused. She didn't really hate him, just a typical
rebellious daughter going through a phase.
Hinori
(..Maybe I was just overthinking things after all..)

At that moment, as Matsuri raised her hand, the hem of her clothes lightly
flipped up. The delicate curve of the girl's waist was exposed, and Hinori
unconsciously stared.
Hinori
(..That was a black stain on her skin just now? Something like a bruise..)

During the small talk with the residents, Hinori couldn't believe what she
saw with her own eyes.. but it was firmly burned into her memory.
There are clothes that have been washed and left here.
Matsuri
"I washed and folded those clothes. They look clean, don't they?"
Hinori
"(W-Wow, you're right.. Ahh, what's this?)"
Hinori
(Th-These panties are so small.. they hardly cover anything..!)

It's an empty bathtub. The drain is plugged and the function to fill it
with hot water is set.

There are some crumpled tissues thrown away. If you pay attention, you can
smell a slight odor..
A

There are novels and fashion magazines for girls. They are probably mainly
brought in by Marisato.
Hinori

(..I wonder when this magazine is from. The cover is worn out, so I can't
tell what year or month it is.)
Hinori
(It's as if it's been here for a very long time..)

This is a beautiful kitchen. It seems like it's used for cooking regularly,
as there are signs of use all around.
It's a wall calendar. The date is stuck in summer.
Hinori

(..I feel like the day of the week is wrong too. What kind of calendar is
this..)
A
A
A pure white toilet. It has been polished until it shines.

There is a large bed that could comfortably sleep two or three adults. Two
pillows are lined up.
Ao

"..Hinori, I was thinking.. wasn't there a room for Marisato-chan in this
house?"
Hinori
"Yeah, besides the living room, this is the only room.."
Hinori also realizes it after Aoi points it out.

According to Marisato, she lives here with her father. And if there's no
room for only Marisato, then.. there's nowhere else for her to sleep
besides this bed.
Ao

"Marisato-chan is certainly still a child.. but is she really young enough
to still be sleeping with her father?"
Hinori

"Well.. she did say earlier that she was waiting for her father to come
home. Maybe she's just a bit of a spoiled child."

While saying that, Hinori notices the discomfort in this house. Marisato
doesn't express any dissatisfaction with the absence of her "mother". She
still does the household chores at a young age and eagerly awaits her
father's return, as if she's a substitute for her mother.

"And Marisato is sleeping on the same bed as her father, with pillows lined
up. In this abnormal village."
Ao

"I feel like I've seen too much unnecessary stuff. Let's go back to
Marisato-chan's place as soon as possible."
Hinori
"Yeah, that's right. It wouldn't be good to keep her waiting too long.."

Hinori is overcome with a dark feeling. It's as if she's peeked into the
secret of an innocent girl. However, she also thinks that maybe Marisato
wanted to show off her secret like a treasure to someone.
Matsuri

"If you go straight down the hallway, you'll find the bathroom. Don't
mistake it for the room next to it, which is the bedroom, okay?"
Matsuri

"If you go straight down the hallway, you'll find the bathroom. Don't
mistake it for the room next to it, which is the bedroom."
